d theory. At the same time, he rethinks a Cavello-Deleuzian approach across the digital and global turns in cinema. Combining clear explanations of complex philosophical arguments with in-depth analyses of the contemporary films Grizzly Man, Amélie, Three Monkeys, and The Headless Woman, Gerrits traces how cinema invents ways of dis/connecting to the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aSkepticism in motion pictures. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847665040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438476650423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438476650/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles